    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - INSTALLATION - MAIN BEARING AND CAP
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="3">
        <title>MAIN BEARING AND CAP</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With acceptable bearing clearance, proceed as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Clean Plastigage(r) from main bearing or crankshaft journal surface.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Coat all bearing surface journals and bolts with clean engine oil.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place No. 1 and No. 6 main bearing caps with lower bearing inserts over crankshaft in
                    the proper location.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Tighten No.1 through No. 6 main bearing cap bolts to special torque value. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050753">7.53</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install rear thrust bearing as follows:</para>
                <seqlist style="arabic">
                    <item>
                        <para>Insert main bearing cap with rear thrust bearing in position as shown in
                            <emph type="bold">Figure
                                <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050754">7.54</hotlnk>
                            </emph>
                            .
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Center rear thrust bearing by moving crankshaft rearward, then forward.</para>
                    </item>
                </seqlist>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Tighten two (2) rear thrust bearing bolts finger-tight, then tighten to the special
                    torque value.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050752" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12190" filename="../figcg1/CG12190.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.52.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050753" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12192" filename="../figcg1/CG12192.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.53.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050754" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg1656" filename="../figeg1/EG1656.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.54.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Check crankshaft end play using a dial indicator as follows: Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e105_166.xml" xrefid="ef1050755">7.55</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <seqlist style="arabic">
                    <item>
                        <para>Mount the dial indicator on crankcase with indicator tip on crankcase flange face.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Lightly pry the crankshaft forward and zero indicator.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Then pry crankshaft rearward and record dial indicator reading. Repeat to assure an
                            accurate reading.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </seqlist>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>If end play exceeds specifications, replace thrust bearing and recheck crankshaft end
                            play. If end play is less than specified, loosen main bearing caps, reposition, torque and
                            recheck end play.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install piston and connecting rod assemblies. Refer to Section 6.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install front cover. Refer to Section 8.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil pump assembly. Refer to Section 9.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
